           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I encountered the following spot though a guildmate of mine the location of the spot is   -327 -430. (follow the left wall as if you were heading to Castle)  At this location there is pathing that will allow you to fear the mob into the wall (once you figure it our your golden) and he just stands there trying to go through the wall. If for some reason your mob get out of this pathing and start heading back to where you pulled him back you pet off sit down and wait for fear to break.  <br /><br />Your targets are feeble rats, and goos. I would avoid Pestilent Rats at all cost they can be snared however they seem to resist it alot and cannot be feared with invoke fear, they dont seem to take root well either.<br /><br />My spell line up is:<br /><br />Deflux (as needed)<br />Pyro (x1)<br />Splurt (x1)<br />Vexing (x1)<br />a nuke (as needed)<br />invoke fear (as needed)<br />dooming darkness (as needed)<br />Feign Death (hopefully you dont need it)<br /><br />at 59 with no aa active I can kill approxmatly 2 for a % of xp.  This is prolly the quickest and easiest experience I have seen for the effort.  I use 3 dots once and its dead.  I am using the EoT pet however it may go quicker with the rouge.  Thought I would pass this information on. There are spiders in the area but I havent had the balls to try them.<br /><br />Gl<br /><br />*edit* added more descrip to location.<br /><br />Halyanth Bloodseer<br />Defiler of 59 Dark Winters<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26777" target="_blank"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26777" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26777</a></a><br />Steel Thunder<br />The Seventh Hammer Server</span id="msg"></font>
