                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I've used this spot a fair bit since 54. you can climb the wall before pulling and that lets you easily check on whether any hidden 'adds' are nearby - very safe, and good XP. <br /><br />The pestilent rats go up to level 54 and only about one in three are fearable. Feeble rats, goos and biles are all fearable and all easy prey.<br /><br />One of the nicest the nice things about this spot is that you get the 'kills withing 5 levels' bonus up to 55 or 56 (and the odd kill at 57) so at those levels the XP flies (AA is nice too - almost a blue per kill).<br /><br />Things to be careful of. You occassionaly get Rankle appearing - a level 55 goo/bile. Doesn't drop anything (the twice I killed him), is snareable but not fearable. Aggro kite him (and pestilent rats if you like) around the corner a little bit in the area leading back towards the ZI. As long as you remember to drop darkness on him regularly you'll be golden (use fear to keep agro - he won't run away, but it stops him turning on your pet).<br /><br />Occasionaly you get spiders pathing across the pull zone and sometimes it just makes more sense to move to another spot.<br /><br />For more info do a search for relevant keywords (PoD feeble goo etc) and you should find a posting from a month or so back giving details of this and a couple of other PoD/PoN spots.<br /><br />Thanks for posting this info Halyanth79, it's a nice spot and worth making those people approaching these level aware of. At your level I would suggest you consider pulling from the castle courtyard (through the bone wall) and aggro kiting. You'll get the '5 level bonus' and you might even get a parchment (or so I'm told - grin). Avoid the SK defilers though - they'll try to snare you and the harm touch can hurt...<br /><br />Rhys <br /><br /><br /><img src="http://www.clement-evans.co.uk/xatan/xatan-eyes.jpg" border="0"></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
